    "b-10-paragraph-proj-6": {
      "id": "b-10-paragraph-proj-6",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "props": {},
      "text": [
        {
          "insert": "A plain text line. Marks render as standard markdown syntax (code innermost, then bold/italic/strike, link outermost); "
        },
        {
          "insert": "reference",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": " marks render as plain text — label if present, else the reference path — because the agent surface is a greppable terminal artifact, not a rendered document. Two quirks worth knowing: a paragraph with empty text renders nothing at all, and the document root is itself a paragraph shell whose own line is always skipped — only its children render."
        }
      ],
      "children": []
